## Objective

Make the Flipper backend deployable to Railway with a single click.

Railway needs:
1. A `Dockerfile` to build and run the backend
2. A `railway.toml` to configure the deployment
3. All environment variables documented clearly
4. Health endpoint verified to respond correctly

No new features. No schema changes. Pure deployment plumbing.

---

## What to Build

### 1. `backend/Dockerfile`

```dockerfile
FROM python:3.12-slim

# Set working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Install system dependencies
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \
    gcc \
    libpq-dev \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Copy requirements and install Python dependencies
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

# Copy application code
COPY . .

# Expose port
EXPOSE 8000

# Run the application
CMD ["uvicorn", "main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]
```

### 2. `railway.toml` (in repo root, not backend/)

```toml
[build]
builder = "dockerfile"
dockerfilePath = "backend/Dockerfile"
dockerContextDir = "backend"

[deploy]
startCommand = "uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT"
healthcheckPath = "/health"
healthcheckTimeout = 30
restartPolicyType = "on_failure"
restartPolicyMaxRetries = 3
```

### 3. `backend/.env.example`

Document every required environment variable. This file is
committed to the repo. The actual `.env` is never committed.

```bash
# ============================================================
# Flipper Backend — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env for local development
# Set these in Railway dashboard for production
# ============================================================

# Database (Railway provides this automatically as DATABASE_URL)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://user:password@localhost:5432/flipper

# Anthropic (required for AI fault detection)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# eBay Browse API (required for listing ingestion)
EBAY_APP_ID=your-ebay-app-id
EBAY_CERT_ID=your-ebay-cert-id

# LinkUp (required for web search enrichment)
LINKUP_API_KEY=your-linkup-api-key

# Stub modes (set to true for development, false for production)
EBAY_STUB=true
LINKUP_STUB=true

# Polling interval in seconds (default 180 = 3 minutes)
POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS=180

# Opportunity alert threshold (default 0.6)
ALERT_SCORE_THRESHOLD=0.6
```

